--------------------------------------------

A) Auth:
- Users can sign up / log in with email + password.
- On first login, user completes onboarding wizard.
- Onboarding is framed as “Choose your stack” (LLM + Server + VPN + Connectors) and Zumo wires it together safely.

B) Onboarding wizard (MUST exist BEFORE Create Employee)

Step 1: Choose LLM Provider (BYO or Buy-through-Zumo)
- Providers: OpenAI / Anthropic / Gemini / OpenAI-compatible
- Two choices per provider:
  (1) BYO: user enters API key (store encrypted). For MVP store placeholder but treat as secret.
  (2) Buy-through-Zumo (marketplace): user selects a plan, goes through a simulated checkout, and Zumo “provisions” credentials automatically.
- IMPORTANT BUSINESS MODEL UI:
  - Display that billing is to the vendor/provider (simulated), with Zumo acting as setup layer.
  - Show transparent cost estimate and Zumo’s value (“we configure securely + manage integration”).
- Set budgets:
  - org daily spend cap
  - per-employee defaults
  - hard stop and alert behavior

Step 2: Choose Virtual Server Provider (BYO or Buy-through-Zumo)
- User chooses where sandboxes run (simulated in MVP):
  - “Bring your own server” (advanced): pick provider, enter server details/SSH key (simulated)
  - “Buy a server via Zumo Marketplace” (recommended): choose vendor + region + size (simulated checkout)
- Providers (simulate): Hetzner / OVH / AWS / GCP / “Custom”
- Must show server selection cards with:
  - region (EU default)
  - cost estimate (vendor billed)
  - security posture default (“locked down”)
- After selection, show provisioning steps (simulated):
  - allocate VM
  - apply firewall rules
  - create non-root runtime user
  - install sandbox runner
  - start supervisor + heartbeat
- End state: “Server Ready”

Step 3: Choose VPN / Private Network Provider (BYO or Buy-through-Zumo)
- Purpose: private-by-default access to sandboxes; no public agent gateway
- Options:
  - Tailscale-like overlay (recommended)
  - WireGuard (advanced)
  - “None (not recommended)” with big warnings
- For MVP, simulate the setup but show:
  - generated config
  - node enrollment
  - private IP assignment
  - “private access enabled” badge
- Explain risks if user selects “None”

Step 4: Connectors (Risk-Aware Access Grant)
- User enables connectors (simulated OAuth):
  Slack, Gmail, HubSpot, GitHub, Google Calendar (stretch Sentry/Linear)
- Each connector card shows:
  - risk level badge (low/med/high)
  - data accessed + actions possible
  - WARNING text: “Start read-only. Writes require policies + approvals.”
  - “danger checklist” modal (token leakage, overbroad scopes, destructive actions)
- Simulated OAuth flow:
  click -> consent screen -> success -> create ConnectedAccount record
- Default to READ-ONLY scopes; require “I understand risks” checkbox for write scopes

After onboarding completes, user lands on main app.

